2500|$|In October 2005, five Toyota {{engineers}} and one Asian AW engineer published an IEEE technical paper detailing a Toyota-approved project to add vehicle-to-grid capability to a Toyota Prius. Although the technical paper described [...] "a method for generating voltage between respective lines of neutral {{points in the}} generator and motor of the THS-II (<b>Toyota</b> <b>Hybrid</b> <b>System)</b> to add a function for generating electricity", it did not state {{whether or not the}} experimental vehicle could be charged through the circuit, as well. However, the vehicle was featured in a Toyota Dream House, and a brochure for the exhibit stated that [...] "the house can supply electricity to the battery packs of the vehicles via the stand {{in the middle of the}} garage", indicating that the vehicle may have been a plug-in hybrid.|$|E
